The Monstrino project source code is made publicly available for the purpose
of learning, studying software architecture, and reviewing implementation
approaches.

This license allows viewing and studying the source code but does not grant
permission to use the code in other software projects.

2. Permitted Uses

You are allowed to:

- View and read the source code
- Study the architecture and implementation
- Fork the repository for personal, non-commercial educational purposes
- Run the official Monstrino project for evaluation or personal exploration

3. Prohibited Uses

You may NOT:

- Use the source code or substantial parts of it in another software project
- Copy the implementation into other repositories or products
